name: Redbud Tree (Cercis canadensis)
description: A beautiful flowering tree with stunning pink blooms in spring before leaves emerge. Grows to be 20-30 feet tall.

name: Japanese Maple (Acer palmatum)
description: A prized ornamental tree known for its delicate leaves with vibrant fall colors. Prefers partial shade and moist soil. Grows to be 15-20 feet tall.

name: Dogwood Tree (Cornus florida)
description: A flowering tree with beautiful white or pink blooms in spring. Prefers full sun to partial shade. Grows to be 15-25 feet tall.

name: Fruiting Apple Tree (Malus domestica)
description: A variety of apple trees with delicious fruits in fall. Choose from different varieties like Gala, Honeycrisp, or Fuji. Grows to be 15-20 feet tall.

name: Citrus Tree (Citrus spp.)
description: Choose from various citrus trees like lemon, orange, or lime. Great for sunny locations and containers. Grows to be 8-15 feet tall depending on the variety.

name: Cypress Tree (Cupressus sempervirens)
description: A tall, evergreen tree with a columnar shape. Perfect for adding a touch of vertical interest to your landscape. Grows to be 40-60 feet tall.

name: Willow Tree (Salix spp.)
description: A graceful tree with weeping branches. Prefers moist soil and full sun. Grows to be 20-40 feet tall depending on the variety.

name: Oak Tree (Quercus spp.)
description: A majestic and long-lived tree with strong branches and lobed leaves. Prefers full sun to partial shade. Choose from various oak varieties. Grows to be 50-100 feet tall depending on the species.
